@startuml EventTriggeredFunction_SysMLv1
' =============================================================================
' SysML v1 (PlantUML) -- Event-triggered Function
' Closes ISO 15288 Cl. 6.4.3.3 b)1) NOTE 6 evidence gap
' (commence / cease conditions on a Function).
' Companion to: EventTriggeredFunction_SysMLv2.sysml
' =============================================================================
title bdd -- Function with commence + cease events (ISO 15288 6.4.3.3 b)1) NOTE 6)

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #FFF8E1
    BorderColor     #7A6100
    ArrowColor      #333333
}

' ---- Two InformationFlow specializations for the event kinds -------------

class CommenceEvent <<block, InformationFlow>> {
    +description    : "ISO 15288 commence condition"
    +protocolStr    : "LIN"
    +bytes          : 1
    +triggerReason  : "NightDetected"
}
class CeaseEvent <<block, InformationFlow>> {
    +description    : "ISO 15288 cease condition"
    +protocolStr    : "LIN"
    +bytes          : 1
    +stopReason     : "DaylightDetected"
}

' ---- Function with two FunctionPorts (commence + cease) ------------------

class HeadlightController <<Function>> {
    +commenceIn : FunctionPort <<in>>
    +ceaseIn    : FunctionPort <<in>>
    +behavior   : ControlHeadlight()
}

' ---- External Actor (Sensor + Source of both events) ---------------------

class AmbientLightSensor <<Sensor, Source>>

' ---- ItemFlow edges: one commence, one cease -----------------------------

AmbientLightSensor ..> HeadlightController : "«InformationFlow» CommenceEvent\n(commence condition)"
AmbientLightSensor ..> HeadlightController : "«InformationFlow» CeaseEvent\n(cease condition)"

note bottom of HeadlightController
  ISO 15288:2023 Cl. 6.4.3.3 b)1) NOTE 6 asks for
  "the conditions under which the system is to
  commence performing that function and the
  conditions under which the system is to cease
  performing that function".

  With the CASCaRA extension both conditions are
  ordinary InformationFlow items connected to a
  FunctionPort -- no special metaclass required.
end note

@enduml
